commit.message:
qa-cmp: normalize symlink permissions in files lists

Not quite sure when this started, but lately started to see symlinks
with lrwxr-xr-x (With ls or stat) on ext4, then mv or cp -a them to
a tmpfs and they're now the lrwxrwxrwx that more used to.

This causes noise when comparing, so let's normalize it.

(Also shellcheck, please, this is not a multidimensional array...
Would've used l????????? but given this hackily matches the whole
string this could pickup a ` (lword ` in filenames)

commit.message:
qa-cmp: be bit more strict with SLOT replacement

Unlike versions, SLOT does not necessarily start with a number,
and if we had e.g. SLOT=e, then "somefile" would become "som*fil*".
So further check that it is not near letters on top of numbers.

PMS states:
  A slot name may contain any of the characters [A-Za-z0-9+_.-].
  It must not begin with a hyphen, a dot or a plus sign.

So thankfully do not have to worry about [+.-], but ignore
_ given SLOT="_something" is rather unusual and _<slot> is
reasonable to replace.
